-------------------------------------------------------------------------
				V0-6
-------------------------------------------------------------------------

V0-6 was the first stable version to go into the repository. It did not
have site support.

-------------------------------------------------------------------------
				V1-0
			Added site support
-------------------------------------------------------------------------

./ecsInstall
	Added site support to ecsInstall (PG 18/May/01).

src/ecsInitCP.data
src/ecsInitMK.data
	Created new copies of the pvload file for Mauna-Kea and Cerro
	Pachon. The old ecsInit.data file was preserved with the setting
	for Mauna-Kea (PG 18/May/01).

startup/startup.vws
startup/startupCP.vws
startup/startupMK.vws
	Copied startup.vws to startupCP.vws and startupMK.vws. Modified
	the prompt to ecs-CP> and ecs-MK> and changed the name of
	ecsInit.data to src/ecsInitCP.data and src/ecsInitMK.data,
	respectively. Removed old startup.vws (PG 18/May/01).

------------------------------------+------------------------------------
				  V1-1
			       Bug fixes
		      Bottom shutter skew detection
-------------------------------------------------------------------------

startup/startup.vws 
startup/startupCP.vws 
startup/startupMK.vws 
	Added Bancomm card code to sync up to the TCS (PG 25/May/01)

startup/.cvsignore
	Added UAE.dist to the list (PG 25/May/01)

dl/status.adl
	Fixed the ECS lights and emergency stop record names. There was a
	missing colon in the record name (PG 25/May/01)

dl/ECS_Display.adl
	Fixed the names of the channels used in the demands of the shutters
	and vent gates (PG 25/May/01).

src/devEcsAbDf1.c
	Updated comments (PG 30/May/01).

src/devEcsAbDf1.c
	Modified the way PARK is handled when the device is already there.
	It now checks whether it has already reached the limits, and also
	it does not check for exact equality of the demand and the position
	because they are not exactly equal (PG 30/May/01).

src/ecsThermal.c
	Changed the OPEN_PASSIVE_VENTS, OPEN_SHELL_DAMPERS, and
	OPEN_ROOF_VENTS macros to clear bits instead of setting them, in
	order to conform with what the PLC expects (PG 31/may/01).

src/ecsThermal.c
	Temporary disabled the following routines by adding a return at
	the beggining of the routine: ahuSetPointAdjust, chillSetPointAdjust,
	exhaustFans, ahuPower, exhaustDampers, and floorDampers until they
	can be tested (PG 31/May/01).

src/ecsThermal.c
	Changed the check for a cardiac arrest in the PRPLC. It now allows
	for a one count difference between the number coming from the PLC
	and the one sent back since sometimes there is a delay in the
	ECS feedback (PG 31/May/01).

capfast/misc.sch
	Removed explicit definition of "ab" macro since it's inherited
	from the parent schematic (PG 31/May/01).

capfast/shuttersStatus.sch
capfast/vgatesStatus.sch
	Changed schematics to limit the shutter position to zero if the
	device position is greater than 150 to prevent getting big
	numbers when the enconders return a negative number (returned
	as a big number by the PLC). For the vent gates the position
	should be in the range (0, 100), for the bottom shutter the value
	should be in the range (0, 60), and for the top shutter it should
	be in the range (0, 96). The top shutter position is meassured
	relative from the lowest point it can reach (~10 degrees), and
	the offset is added afterwards (PG 31/May/01).

src/ecsFault.c
dl/motorFault.adl
	Added detection for bottom shutter skewing and the skew encoder
	fault (PG 12/May/01).

src/ecMisc.c
	Forced CAR status of the thermal system so activeC will not be in
	an error condition while the PRPLC is not connected (PG 13/Jun/01).

src/ecCommands.c
	Removed debug printErr() statements (PG 13/Jun/01).

src/ecsMotor.h
src/ecsFault.c
src/devEcsAbDf1.c
	Added SKEWING define and modified the code to set and check for
	this new condition (PG 13/Jun/01).

src/ecsInit.data
src/ecsInitCP.data
src/ecsInitMK.data
	Enabled motion interlock. This interlock had beed bypassed in the
	early days because the interface to the GIS was not ready, but now
	this si not true anymore. The thermal interlock is still bypassed
	because there are no interlocks of this type defined (PG 14/Jun/01).

