				V1-2
			     Bug fixes
-------------------------------------------------------------------------

ecsInstall
Makefile.subdirs
	Added "-s Makefile.subdirs" in ecsInstall and cleaned garbage
	from Makefile.subdirs (PG 10/Aug/01).

-------------------------------------------------------------------------
				V1-4
			     Bug fixes
	NOTE: V1-3 was a dead version because of problems with tags
-------------------------------------------------------------------------

ecsInstall
src/ecsInit.data
	Removed ecsInit.data and modified ecsInstall so it will now copy
	ecsInitCP.data or ecsInitMK.data to ecsInit.data depending on the
	site. This is necessary because the code reloads ecsInit.data
	(fixed name) when an INIT is performed (PG 10/Oct/01).

src/ecsInitCP.data
	Disabled motion interlock because it was dicovered that the GIS
	PLC is not sending the intelock signals to the ECS (PG 10/Oct/01).

-------------------------------------------------------------------------
				V2-0
			     Port to GEM7

In order to avoid build problems (seen in previous attempts) an empty
tree was created using applSetup.pl and the code was copied one directory
at a time. All the CVS directories were tared from the version in the
repository and restored in the new directory.
-------------------------------------------------------------------------

adl/*.adl
adl/*.sh
	Copied all *.adl files and shel scripts into this directory. The
	file colors.adl was copied as well since the color rules for the
	ECS are different (PG 22/Mar/02).

adl/ecs_diag.sh
adl/ecs_disp.sh
adl/ecs_dm.sh
adl/ecsSim_dm.sh
adl/test_dm.sh
	Changed dm2.4 to dm2-4 (PG 22/Mar/02).

dbRecType.ascii
devSup.ascii
drvSup.ascii
choiceEcsMotor.h
choiceRec.ascii
ecsMotorRecord.ascii
	Copied files from the ascii directory. These are not needed in
	GEM7, but they were copied for archiving purposes (PG 22/Mar/02).

capfast/*.sch
capfast/*.sym
p216a
printCF
printDome
printEcs
printMech
printMotorSim
printSad
printShutters
printSim
printSoft
printStatus
printThermalSim
printVgates
	Copied capfast files and auxiliary scripts (PG 22/Mar/02).

capfast/Makefile.Host
	Added the following line to the flag declarations:

		E2DB_SYSFLAGS = -ate -d ../edb.def

	to make the database include the ECS Motor record. Otherwise
	the database ends up having fewer records (PG 22/Mar/02).

capfast/Makefile.Host
	Changed the DATA definition to:

		DATA = ecs.db ecsSim.db ecsSad.db

	to generate the three ECS databases (PG 22/Mar/02).

capfast/edb.def
	Copied a fresh copy of edb.def from the EPICS tree and added the
	ECS motor entry from the old file (PG 22/Mar/02).

NOTE:
	When recompiling the capfast directory it was found that there
	was one record missing from the database (305 records instead of
	306). This is okay since the ECS uses the wait record in the
	parkNew1.sch and this code needs to be replaced anyway.

ecsInstall
	Copied old file and changed invokation of applSetup to

	    applSetup.pl -T mv167 -T ppc604 \
			 -I adl -I alh -I capfast -I src -I startup -I db \
			 -S $site $1 > $2 2>&1

	Also removed cp's of ecsInitCP.data and ecsInitMK.data to
	ecsInit.data because the INIT file name problem will be handled
	in a better way (PG 22/Mar/02).

config/CONFIG.Defs
	Changed APPLIC_IOCPATH and APPLIC_SITE to:

		APPLIC_IOCPATH = icarus:/gemini/epics3.13.4/ecs/V2-0
		APPLIC_SITE = CP

	This had to be done by hand since it was not done when applSetup
	was run for the first time (PG 22/Mar/02).

src/*.c
src/*.h
src/*.st*
	Copied files from old version. An old version of ecsThermal.c
	(ecsThermal.bw) was not copied (PG 22/Mar/02).

src/abDev.dbd
src/ecsMotorRecord.dbd
	Added definition files for the ECS motor record and the Allen
	Bradley device support (PG 22/Mar/02).

src/Makefile.Vx
	Added
		RECTYPES = ecsMotorRecord.h
	and
		DBDINSTALL  = ecsMotorRecord.dbd
		DBDINSTALL += abDev.dbd
	and
		LIBOBJS += abLog.o
		LIBOBJS += devEcsAbDf1.o
		LIBOBJS += drvAbDf1.o
		LIBOBJS += drvSerial.o
		LIBOBJS += ecCommands.o
		LIBOBJS += ecHealth.o
		LIBOBJS += ecInterlocks.o
		LIBOBJS += ecMisc.o
		LIBOBJS += ecSIR.o
		LIBOBJS += ecsFault.o
		LIBOBJS += ecsThermal.o
		LIBOBJS += fakeDevice.o
		LIBOBJS += recEcsMotor.o
	and
		LIBNAME = libEcs
	and
		DATA    += ../ecsInitCP.pv
		DATA    += ../ecsInitMK.pv
		DATA    += ../ecsSimInit.pv

	to match the old file (PG 22/Mar/02).

startup/startupCP.vws
startup/startupMK.vws
